132
00:08:07,420 --> 00:08:09,651
Brother hit her over
the head with a lamp.

133
00:08:10,757 --> 00:08:12,419
Hi, Amy. This is Dr. Rasgotra.

134
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:15,721
- Hi.
- Hi. This is Cullum.

135
00:08:15,895 --> 00:08:18,421
- I can't get up.
- Oh, here. Let me help you. Here.

136
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:20,760
She's too fat to get up.

137
00:08:35,382 --> 00:08:37,283
Oww.

138
00:08:37,450 --> 00:08:40,113
Oh, my goodness. That
was quite the fall, young lady.

139
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:42,619
- Oh, thank you. HERB:
Okay. Can you believe it?

140
00:08:42,789 --> 00:08:46,954
There you go. All this ice and
not a speck of salt to be seen.

141
00:08:47,127 --> 00:08:51,223
I think the hospital is negligent
and responsible for your injury.

142
00:08:51,398 --> 00:08:52,957
Oh, no. I don't have an injury.

143
00:08:53,566 --> 00:08:56,730
Well, gonna feel okay
probably for the first 24 hours.

144
00:08:56,903 --> 00:08:58,462
And then the pain develops.

145
00:08:58,638 --> 00:09:01,267
You could be looking at
long-term disability from...

146
00:09:01,441 --> 00:09:03,740
for example, lumbar
myofascial strain...

147
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:07,312
or disc herniation
syndrome with radiculopathy.

148
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,675
It's just a bruise.

149
00:09:08,848 --> 00:09:11,317
I think an MRI is
indicated definitely.

150
00:09:11,484 --> 00:09:13,817
- Are you a doctor?
- Uh, no. Attorney.

151
00:09:14,254 --> 00:09:17,088
Herb Spivak, attorney
at law. My card.

152
00:09:18,591 --> 00:09:21,493
Dr. Lewis, OIG, line 2. Claiming
we transferred an unstable patient.

153
00:09:21,661 --> 00:09:23,653
- You're a doctor, huh?
- Yeah.

154
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:25,492
Let me tell you something.

155
00:09:25,665 --> 00:09:27,827
You never know when you're
gonna need more protection.

156
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:30,937
These hospital bigwigs
will let you hang out to dry...

157
00:09:31,104 --> 00:09:32,470
if you ever get sued.

158
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:36,337
If you solicit any more patients in my
bay, I will have you forcibly removed.

159
00:09:36,876 --> 00:09:39,277
How about a free pen?

160
00:09:41,314 --> 00:09:42,714
Follow my finger, um...

161
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:44,612
- Amy.
- Thank you.

162
00:09:44,784 --> 00:09:46,047
Hi, I'm Dr. Kovac.

163
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,812
- Neela, present to me when you're done.
- Oh, okay.

164
00:09:48,988 --> 00:09:51,856
- Am I in some sort of trouble?
- No, no. Just keep going.

165
00:09:52,492 --> 00:09:54,654
- It's Mr. Meacham, right?
- The one and only.

166
00:09:54,828 --> 00:09:56,990
Tell me about your pain.
Did you have an injury?

167
00:09:57,163 --> 00:10:00,031
- I was moving boxes at work.
- Where do you work?

168
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,691
I used to work as a lumberjack.

169
00:10:01,868 --> 00:10:04,167
But I couldn't hack it,
so they gave me the ax.

170
00:10:04,337 --> 00:10:06,329
Is it worse when you walk?

171
00:10:07,006 --> 00:10:10,204
- Can I help with something, Dr. Kovac?
- Just observing.

172
00:10:10,376 --> 00:10:12,208
- You have pain in any of the joints?
- No.

173
00:10:12,378 --> 00:10:14,711
Can you get a postural
vitals for me in Exam 2?

174
00:10:14,881 --> 00:10:18,010
