Neela up for suturing, I got a Foley...

175
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:23,088
an NG, two IVs to start, and a
five-page patient-transfer summary.

176
00:10:24,324 --> 00:10:26,054
I got your tray.

177
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,586
Amy, I talked to your
mom. She's on her way.

178
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:32,891
Oh, my foster mom.
He's her real son.

179
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,901
- How long have you been with them?
- Since last March. Ow!

180
00:10:36,069 --> 00:10:37,367
Sorry.

181
00:10:37,537 --> 00:10:39,904
Uh, that was lidocaine
to numb up your cut.

182
00:10:40,073 --> 00:10:41,735
Die! Ha!

183
00:10:42,442 --> 00:10:44,070
I hope he's
referring to his game.

184
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:47,744
Cullum needs his meds adjusted.
That's why he has tantrums.

185
00:10:47,914 --> 00:10:49,780
- Die, die, die.
- Is that what happened?

186
00:10:49,949 --> 00:10:51,713
- He lost his temper?
- Kind of.

187
00:10:51,885 --> 00:10:55,083
- What meds is he on?
- Adderall and Depakote for ADHD...

188
00:10:55,255 --> 00:10:56,689
and ODD.

189
00:10:58,258 --> 00:11:01,057
I'll be back to sew you up.

190
00:11:03,596 --> 00:11:06,862
Does it seem like every 10-year-old
boy you see nowadays has ADHD?

191
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:08,763
ADHD, a Game Boy and an iPod.

192
00:11:08,935 --> 00:11:11,803
Foster kid, head injury,
unsupervised home...

193
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:14,566
- We should call Social Work.
- I think Wendall's on.

194
00:11:14,741 --> 00:11:17,768
- Look, I know how to do an H &
