195
00:11:17,944 --> 00:11:20,914
Hold on. How long did you let
him talk before interrupting him?

196
00:11:21,948 --> 00:11:24,110
- Twenty, 30 seconds.
- Four.

197
00:11:24,284 --> 00:11:27,152
- What color were his eyes?
- I don't know. We weren't on a date.

198
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:29,447
Didn't make eye contact.
Listen to his heart?

199
00:11:29,622 --> 00:11:31,955
The guy had a twisted knee.
- Doesn't matter.

200
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:36,221
Listen to his heart to show you care
and that you're paying attention to detail.

201
00:11:36,396 --> 00:11:38,558
- I don't have time.
- It takes one minute.

202
00:11:38,731 --> 00:11:43,396
Makes a difference between your patient
feeling taken care of and feeling ignored.

203
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:46,301
We got patients that have
been waiting over nine hours.

204
00:11:46,472 --> 00:11:48,805
Believe me, they
already feel ignored.

205
00:11:52,679 --> 00:11:56,309
- You ready to present?
- I think I need to redo my exam.

206
00:11:56,482 --> 00:11:58,615
Listen, it's about
connecting better. If

207
00:11:58,639 --> 00:12:01,011
your patients trust
you, she'll heal faster.

208
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:04,123
- That's what all the studies say, okay?
- Okay.

209
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:08,519
I find it really distracting working
with somebody so good-looking.

210
00:12:08,695 --> 00:12:10,129
Who? Dr. Kovac?

211
00:12:10,296 --> 00:12:12,162
Oh, come on. Don't
pretend he's not hot.

212
00:12:12,332 --> 00:12:14,028
I don't know, you
just get used to it.

213
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,465
- Yeah. But he's gorgeous.
- Who's gorgeous?

214
00:12:16,636 --> 00:12:18,434
Got a John Doe.

215
00:12:18,605 --> 00:12:20,540
