00:12:57,877 --> 00:13:02,338
Okay. Now make your incision from
the anterior tibia to the medial malleolus.

231
00:13:03,383 --> 00:13:05,750
You a doctor? I think
I'm having an aneurysm.

232
00:13:05,952 --> 00:13:08,547
Sir, please wait back inside
for a doctor to get to you.

233
00:13:08,721 --> 00:13:11,054
- Pratt, you got a sec?
- I could be having a stroke!

234
00:13:11,224 --> 00:13:13,659
- Probably a headache.
- They might cut a resident?

235
00:13:13,826 --> 00:13:15,692
I'm gonna sue you
if I end up paralyzed.

236
00:13:15,862 --> 00:13:17,421
- Why are you following me?
- I'm not.

237
00:13:17,597 --> 00:13:19,088
- Gentlemen, please!
- I'm serious.

238
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:20,756
My attorney's
office is right there.

239
00:13:20,967 --> 00:13:22,607
<i>Did a doctor screw you up?</i>

240
00:13:22,902 --> 00:13:26,100
<i>Come visit the
Mobile Law Office...</i>

241
00:13:26,272 --> 00:13:29,765
<i>of Herb W. Spivak.</i>

242
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:33,276
He's had two rounds of epi and
atropine. Holding compressions.

243
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:35,914
One more tie on the distal segment.
- Okay.

244
00:13:36,082 --> 00:13:38,244
Asystole. How much longer?

245
00:13:38,418 --> 00:13:40,717
Until the third liter's in.

246
00:13:41,554 --> 00:13:44,183
Sam, resume compressions.

247
00:13:49,595 --> 00:13:52,030
Now, get your femoral pulse.

248
00:13:53,099 --> 00:13:55,967
- Can't quite get one.
- It's because he bled out.

249
00:13:56,135 --> 00:13:58,070
Third liter's in.

250
00:13:58,638 --> 00:14:00,630
Uh, no pulse. Okay, that's it.

251
00:14:00,807 --> 00:14:02,537
Time of death, 9:52.

252
00:14:02,709 --> 00:14:06,111
- Thanks for showing me.
- Yeah. Write up your note. I'll co-sign.

253
00:14:06,279 --> 00:14:08,271
Any identifying marks?

254
00:14:08,448 --> 00:14:10,110
Brand-new sneakers, blue.

255
00:14:10,283 --> 00:14:13,253
Wonder what he was thinking
when he put those on this morning?

256
00:14:16,956 --> 00:14:18,481
- What?
- Had it been just us...

257
00:14:18,658 --> 00:14:20,286
you would've
pronounced him dead.

258
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:22,952
- He was hypovolemic.
- He never had a pulse.

259
00:14:23,129 --> 00:14:25,564
There was a chance he
might respond to a fluid bolus.

260
00:14:25,732 --> 00:14:28,998
If you were really serious, you
would have ordered the O-neg.

261
00:14:29,168 --> 00:14:33,162
Someday they might find themselves with
no rapid infuser or a central-line kit.

262
00:14:33,339 --> 00:14:35,579
If they know how to do a
cutdown, they could save a life.

263
00:14:35,675 --> 00:14:39,635
I can't afford to waste time on teaching
cases when there's real work to do.

264
00:14:39,812 --> 00:14:41,576
This is what we
do. We train doctors.

265
00:14:41,748 --> 00:14:45,116
Sometimes that means running through
codes so residents learn procedures.

266
00:14:45,284 --> 00:14:49,016
- I mean, it's a teaching hospital.
- Yeah! It's also a real hospital...

267
00:14:49,188 --> 00:14:51,419
with patients who
didn't get antibiotics...

268
00:14:51,591 --> 00:14:53,651
because I was in here
doing compressions.

269
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:57,422
So you did some extra compressions.
What are you really mad about?

270
00:14:59,365 --> 00:15:02,426
Are you in all seriousness telling
me for the second time today...

271
00:15:02,602 --> 00:15:05,572
that I am not mad about
what I'm really mad about?

272
00:15:05,838 --> 00:15:08,171
I have no idea
what you just said.

273
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:12,375
Forget it.

274
00:15:18,518 --> 00:15:20,851
Nine hundred dollars for
a studio in Andersonville.

275
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:23,615
- What happened? Abby kick you out?
- No.

276
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:25,349
- Yes.
- When's she coming in?

277
00:15:25,525 --> 00:15:27,187
Shift starts at 2.

278
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:29,488
You know, I've missed her.

279
00:15:30,730 --> 00:15:31,959
What? I have.

280
00:15:32,131 --> 00:15:34,862
I just got a two-bedroom
sublet on North and Oakley...

281
00:15:35,034 --> 00:15:36,525
for just 1000 a month.

282
00:15:36,702 --> 00:15:37,965
Wicker Park.

283
00:15:38,137 --> 00:15:40,072
But my roommate
just flaked out on me.

284
00:15:40,239 --> 00:15:42,435
Back in rehab, huh?

285
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:45,043
You wouldn't happen
to be interested in, um...?

286
00:15:45,211 --> 00:15:46,702
You mean you and me?

287
00:15:46,879 --> 00:15:50,646
- Five hundred's better than a grand.
- Thanks. I'll think about it.

288
00:15:50,883 --> 00:15:52,374
Morris.

289
00:15:55,121 --> 00:15:56,783
Hey, isn't that
our local shyster?

290
00:15:58,324 --> 00:16:01,419
- Damn.
- No, no, no. Allow me.

291
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,323
Go for it, Archie.

292
00:16:05,398 --> 00:16:07,458
Hi, I'm looking for
a Dr. Ras-goostra.

293
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,124
Rasgotra? That's me.

294
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:12,238
Hi. I'm Kitty Peyser. I'm
Amy's foster mom. Is she okay?

295
00:16:12,405 --> 00:16:15,239
She's fine. She's just needs
some stitches and a tetanus shot.

296
00:16:15,408 --> 00:16:18,435
I heard they got in a fight. Cullum's
not bad. He needs his meds.

297
00:16:18,611 --> 00:16:21,137
Perhaps you'd like to
talk to our social worker?

298
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:22,942
No, I just wanna
see my daughter.

299
00:16:23,115 --> 00:16:25,277
I should tell you, I had
to notify Social Work.

300
00:16:25,451 --> 00:16:27,977
- They'll probably be contacting DCFS.
- What?

301
00:16:28,154 --> 00:16:32,091
- When children come in with suspicious...
- No, no, no, come on. Hey, kids fight.

302
00:16:32,258 --> 00:16:34,750
- It's a standard situation.
- There is no situation.

303
00:16:34,927 --> 00:16:36,361
Mrs. Peyser...

304
00:16:36,562 --> 00:16:40,863
Look, don't do this to us. We
love Amy. They'll take her away.

305
00:16:42,068 --> 00:16:44,094
- Amy, I'm here.
- Hi.

306
00:16:46,172 --> 00:16:48,971
Multiple GSWs. Gang shootout
on the corner of 51st and King.

307
00:16:49,141 --> 00:16:52,009
Tachy at 138. BP, 85 palp.
- I'll take the airway.

308
00:16:52,445 --> 00:16:54,676
- What do you got? PRATT:
Three gunshots to the abdomen.

309
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:56,372
Run it, Pratt.

310
00:16:56,582 --> 00:16:59,882
No breath sounds on the left.
Morris, chest tube. Jane, subclavian.

311
00:17:00,086 --> 00:17:02,453
Ray, stop staring at the
monitor and concentrate.

312
00:17:02,622 --> 00:17:04,784
I've never done a subclavian.
- Hey!

313
00:17:04,957 --> 00:17:08,121
It's time to buck up. Central-line
kit. Did you get rid of Herb yet?

314
00:17:08,294 --> 00:17:10,889
No. He says he has a client
at the hospital revising her will.

315
00:17:11,097 --> 00:17:13,089
Ho-ho. He is wily, that one.

316
00:17:15,001 --> 00:17:16,970
- Stay in the midline, Ray.
- I got it.

317
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:20,734
Does he need atropine or epi?

318
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:23,141
No. He needs oxygen.
The tube's not in.

319
00:17:23,309 --> 00:17:24,333
Oh, great.

320
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:26,741
You have to see it
go through the cords.

321
00:17:26,913 --> 00:17:28,814
- Give me the blade.
- Let me try again.

322
00:17:28,981 --> 00:17:30,415
Maybe next time. Tube.

323
00:17:30,917 --> 00:17:33,182
- Pratt, why don't you try teaching?
- Oh, okay.

324
00:17:33,352 --> 00:17:34,615
You did it wrong. Watch me.

325
00:17:36,756 --> 00:17:38,884
Call Surgery. This
guy needs an ex-lap.

326
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:40,651
And I'm in.

327
00:17:40,826 --> 00:17:43,193
See? It's just that simple.

328
00:17:43,362 --> 00:17:46,059
- Thank you, Greg.
- Anytime, Ray.

329
00:17:46,232 --> 00:17:47,666
Am I gonna have a scar?

330
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:49,324
Just a little line.

331
00:17:49,502 --> 00:17:51,596
We'll take you to
Darlene's salon tomorrow.

332
00:17:51,771 --> 00:17:53,501
- We'll get you bangs.
- That'd be nice.

333
00:17:53,673 --> 00:17:55,767
Keep the wound dry
till the stitches come out.

334
00:17:55,942 --> 00:17:57,501
So no baths and no swimming.

335
00:17:58,411 --> 00:17:59,709
I should go check on Cullum.

336
00:18:00,179 --> 00:18:02,444
Mary, can you take Mrs.
Peyser to the family room?

337
00:18:02,648 --> 00:18:04,241
- Sure.
- Don't worry, Amy.

338
00:18:04,417 --> 00:18:06,511
Everything's gonna be fine.

339
00:18:17,964 --> 00:18:19,728
So Neosporin twice a day...

340
00:18:19,899 --> 00:18:23,028
and come back if it's red,
painful or draining fluid.

341
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:28,803
Does your cut hurt?

342
00:18:36,816 --> 00:18:39,945
- What's wrong?
- I know what's gonna happen.

343
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,644
Once you call in Social Work...

344
00:18:41,821 --> 00:18:46,259
- Amy, don't get ahead of yourself.
- I can't leave. They need me.

345
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:51,497
I give Cullum his pills every
morning, and I get him ready for school.

346
00:18:51,697 --> 00:18:54,462
That's a lot of responsibility
for a girl your age.

347
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:58,000
It's the only home where I
haven't been beaten up or ignored.

348
00:18:58,204 --> 00:19:00,435
Kitty loves me. She needs me.

349
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:03,804
My whole life, I've
never felt that before.

350
00:19:11,951 --> 00:19:13,351
- Sam.
- Yeah?

351
00:19:13,519 --> 00:19:15,681
Did you already call Social
Work on Amy Packer?

352
00:19:15,855 --> 00:19:17,756
Yeah. Wendall will be down soon.

353
00:19:19,859 --> 00:19:21,589
What is that?

354
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:24,258
It's still caffeine.

355
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:26,422
Call Wendall back and
tell her not to bother?

356
00:19:26,599 --> 00:19:29,535
- Why?
- I was too quick. I should have waited.

357
00:19:29,735 --> 00:19:32,330
She's a foster kid. We
always call Social Work.

358
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:40,169
- What are you doing?
- Stabbing me to death.

359
00:19:40,346 --> 00:19:42,315
I think he's dehydrated.

360
00:19:42,481 --> 00:19:44,712
Ow! Do I look like
a pincushion to you?

361
00:19:44,884 --> 00:19:47,285
He's my patient. Why are
you torturing my patient?

362
00:19:47,453 --> 00:19:50,548
Jane said Dr. Kovac told her
you needed some help today.

363
00:19:51,457 --> 00:19:52,652
Sats, 79. Barely any pulse.

364
00:19:52,825 --> 00:19:55,294
Let me do it. You can
practice later on a dummy.

365
00:19:55,461 --> 00:19:58,329
- I can't get the tube into the space.
- Use a twisting motion.

366
00:19:58,497 --> 00:20:01,524
- Systolic's only 60. Cycle the DynaMap.
- Your incision big enough?

367
00:20:01,701 --> 00:20:02,964
- I don't know.
- Morris.

368
00:20:03,135 --> 00:20:06,299
- You've done a chest tube before, right?
- P.E.A. Lost the pulse.

369
00:20:06,472 --> 00:20:08,737
- Give me the tube. Out of the way.
- No, I got it.

370
00:20:08,908 --> 00:20:12,208
- You need to manage your team.
- I don't know how to explain any better.

371
00:20:12,378 --> 00:20:14,643
- Bradying down to 50.
- Amp of epi.

372
00:20:14,814 --> 00:20:18,910
- You criticize and make them nervous.
- What do you think you're doing to me?

373
00:20:19,085 --> 00:20:20,883
Kid doesn't have
time for them to learn.

374
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:23,522
- Hello. We can hear you.
- We're standing right here.

375
00:20:23,723 --> 00:20:25,282
He's pulseless.

376
00:20:26,325 --> 00:20:27,793
Check it again.

377
00:20:29,662 --> 00:20:32,325
- Good carotid.
- Tension pneumo.

378
00:20:32,665 --> 00:20:35,396
- It's a common cause of P.E.A.
- His sats are rising.

379
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:38,902
So do you mind if I ask our
Residents to roll him up to the O.R.?

380
00:20:39,071 --> 00:20:42,007
Or do you think that that
would hurt their feelings?

381
00:20:45,344 --> 00:20:46,676
What was that all about?

382
00:20:46,846 --> 00:20:50,840
That was an intubation, a chest tube
and a central-line in under 15 minutes.

383
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:53,008
The point is not
to do it all yourself.

384
00:20:53,419 --> 00:20:55,547
Because you all had a
group hug this morning...

385
00:20:55,721 --> 00:20:58,384
do I have to listen to this
touchy-feely crap all day?

386
00:20:58,557 --> 00:21:00,856
- Yeah.
- I'm not an intern, okay?

387
00:21:01,026 --> 00:21:02,289
So stop acting like one.

388
00:21:02,461 --> 00:21:05,397
You have people under you.
You're responsible for teaching them.

389
00:21:05,564 --> 00:21:08,261
So are you gonna build
their confidence or destroy it?

390
00:21:08,434 --> 00:21:12,530
Well, if the choice is between building
up self-esteem and saving my patient...

391
00:21:12,705 --> 00:21:15,937
I'm gonna have to go
with my patient every time.

392
00:21:28,387 --> 00:21:30,151
I don't know, they
were unsupervised.

393
00:21:30,356 --> 00:21:32,882
The mother seems overwhelmed,
the brother has problems.

394
00:21:33,058 --> 00:21:34,253
This is her fifth home.

395
00:21:34,426 --> 00:21:38,261
It's not a perfect family, but she
says it's the best she's ever had.

396
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:42,231
I haven't spoken to their caseworker.
Safest thing is pull her from the home.

397
00:21:42,401 --> 00:21:45,496
She's happy there. No guarantee
things will be better anywhere else.

398
00:21:45,671 --> 00:21:47,799
You guys talking
about that foster kid?

399
00:21:48,908 --> 00:21:51,605
They're happy together. The
family seems to be working.

400
00:21:52,745 --> 00:21:55,977
If the mom agrees to parenting
classes, I'll consider re-evaluating...

401
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:58,743
Neela, some landlord
for you on line two.

402
00:21:58,918 --> 00:22:01,581
I'll take it in Admit. She'll
do whatever you need.

403
00:22:02,288 --> 00:22:05,486
I tell you, I find hospital
conditions absolutely woeful.

404
00:22:05,658 --> 00:22:08,924
- Are you overworked and underpaid?
- I'm a nurse.

405
00:22:09,094 --> 00:22:12,622
- You can't be back here. Get out.
- You can't kick me out. I'm a patient.

406
00:22:12,798 --> 00:22:15,962
- What?
- That's right. Very bad sore throat.

407
00:22:16,135 --> 00:22:17,933
- Sore throat?
- I signed in. Yeah.

408
00:22:18,103 --> 00:22:20,971
I know you guys are backed
up, so don't worry, I'll wait.

409
00:22:21,140 --> 00:22:25,168
Just take all the time you need.
I'm gonna fetch me a lozenge.

410
00:22:26,111 --> 00:22:28,478
- Haldol and hard restraints?
- Huh?

411
00:22:28,647 --> 00:22:32,015
We could treat him like a psych
patient with delusions of being a lawyer.

412
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:33,482
- Abby?
- Abby.

413
00:22:33,652 --> 00:22:36,281
- Hi.
- Hi.

414
00:22:36,455 --> 00:22:38,151
- Um, are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

415
00:22:38,324 --> 00:22:39,656
- Good to see you.
- You too.

416
00:22:39,825 --> 00:22:42,454
- Oh, my God, Abby. Did you get my card?
- Yeah. Thank you.

417
00:22:42,628 --> 00:22:44,153
I prayed for you.

418
00:22:44,330 --> 00:22:48,392
No windows at all? Shared
bathroom? Is that even legal here?

419
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:52,163
- Abby finally kicked her out?
- Well, how much a month?

420
00:22:53,138 --> 00:22:55,801
Whew. It's ugly out there.

421
00:22:57,142 --> 00:23:02,376
You usually do early shifts, right?
So you can go for gigs with your band?

422
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:05,382
Yeah. And if you stick to
your late shifts and overnights...

423
00:23:05,551 --> 00:23:08,146
Weeks could go by, we
might never see each other.

424
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,549
Months even.

425
00:23:11,991 --> 00:23:13,653
Welcome, roomie.

426
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:18,823
God, I'm gonna regret this.

427
00:23:21,166 --> 00:23:24,898
Excuse me, please. Excuse
me. I need to see my grandson.

428
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:27,039
- What's his name?
- Michael. Michael Barnes.

429
00:23:27,206 --> 00:23:30,665
- His friends said he got shot.
- I don't see the name.

430
00:23:30,976 --> 00:23:36,347
He's 16. He was wearing jeans,
a gray T-shirt and sneakers.

431
00:23:36,515 --> 00:23:39,679
- Blue sneakers?
- Yes. Yes. You saw him?

432
00:23:39,852 --> 00:23:42,412
A patient came in earlier
matching that description.

433
00:23:42,588 --> 00:23:44,682
- Is he okay?
- If you'd like to take a seat...

434
00:23:44,857 --> 00:23:48,726
- I can get the Attending for you.
- Wait a minute. Has something happened?

435
00:23:48,894 --> 00:23:50,123
- Ma'am...
- Is he dead?

436
00:23:50,296 --> 00:23:52,269
I can't give any more
information until...

437
00:23:52,293 --> 00:23:53,926
Is he okay? Why
can't you tell me?

438
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:56,796
- Ma'am, please calm down.
- Where is he? I need to see him.

439
00:23:57,002 --> 00:23:59,369
- If you'd like to take a seat...
- Where's my grandson?

440
00:23:59,538 --> 00:24:03,031
- We can't confirm anything until...
- His name is Michael Barnes. Michael?

441
00:24:03,208 --> 00:24:06,303
We can't confirm anything
until the body's been ID'd.

442
00:24:07,513 --> 00:24:09,106
What?

443
00:24:11,083 --> 00:24:12,312
Oh, God.

444
00:24:14,653 --> 00:24:16,451
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to...

445
00:24:18,924 --> 00:24:21,052
Just let me go and
get the Attending. I'm...

446
00:24:21,226 --> 00:24:24,628
Ma'am, if you'd just like to take a
seat, and I'm sure the Attending can...

447
00:24:24,797 --> 00:24:28,928
Oh, Michael. God.

448
00:24:36,075 --> 00:24:39,068
- Where's the grandmother now?
- Crying it out in the family room.

449
00:24:39,244 --> 00:24:42,180
I guess Neela needs to work
a little on her death notification.

450
00:24:42,348 --> 00:24:45,546
A little? Grandma's traumatized. I
can't believe we didn't have to sedate her.

451
00:24:45,718 --> 00:24:49,587
You can't teach basic people-skills.
You know how to relate to people or not.

452
00:24:49,755 --> 00:24:51,223
- Croissant?
- I'll go talk to her.

453
00:24:51,390 --> 00:24:53,256
You realize you're
just encouraging him.

454
00:24:53,425 --> 00:24:56,418
Just because he's a shark doesn't
mean we can't eat his pastries.

455
00:24:58,030 --> 00:25:00,124
Hey, who's on call for
general surgery tonight?

456
00:25:00,299 --> 00:25:01,562
- Sung.
- Okay.

457
00:25:01,734 --> 00:25:04,260
I have to track down an
abdominal series from Radiology.

458
00:25:04,436 --> 00:25:07,964
