shaman and a guru, so I'm all good.

466
00:25:28,727 --> 00:25:30,593
That was Wendall,
our social worker.

467
00:25:30,763 --> 00:25:33,062
She's getting information
from your foster mom.

468
00:25:33,232 --> 00:25:35,167
- She's not gonna take me away?
- No.

469
00:25:35,467 --> 00:25:37,402
Your foster mom's
gonna take some classes.

470
00:25:37,569 --> 00:25:41,336
You and Cullum will start an after-school
program so you can go home together.

471
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,304
- Oh, thank you.
- You're welcome.

472
00:25:43,475 --> 00:25:45,239
Thank you, thank you.

473
00:25:49,481 --> 00:25:52,280
Mary, can you take Amy up
to the seventh floor, please?

474
00:25:52,451 --> 00:25:54,784
- Sure.
- They'll be waiting for you.

475
00:26:02,795 --> 00:26:06,129
- So you convinced Social Work, huh?
- It seems so.

476
00:26:06,298 --> 00:26:09,826
- Good job.
- I took your advice. I tried to connect.

477
00:26:10,002 --> 00:26:13,097
Didn't do such a good job
with the grandmother though.

478
00:26:13,372 --> 00:26:16,342
You and Dr. Lewis must
think I'm a complete idiot.

479
00:26:16,508 --> 00:26:20,809
No, no. You're just inexperienced.
Hey, hey, hey, come here.

480
00:26:21,380 --> 00:26:26,216
First, you bring them into the family
room for a death notification. Sit down.

481
00:26:27,119 --> 00:26:29,315
Somewhere away from
the patients and the staff.

482
00:26:29,488 --> 00:26:32,652
- She just got so hysterical.
- Make sure they are sitting down.

483
00:26:32,825 --> 00:26:35,795
Don't be evasive and
don't use euphemisms.

484
00:26:35,961 --> 00:26:38,988
- Use the word "dead" and the word "is."
- I know all this.

485
00:26:39,164 --> 00:26:43,625
Give them a tissue. Look them
in the eye and make a connection.

486
00:26:44,903 --> 00:26:48,340
Then just say, "I'm very sorry."

487
00:26:54,179 --> 00:26:57,581
- It's okay.
- I suck.

488
00:26:57,749 --> 00:27:02,119
No, you don't suck.
You're still learning.

489
00:27:13,632 --> 00:27:18,332
I can't believe this. I'm in
a wedding next weekend.

490
00:27:19,538 --> 00:27:24,374
- One percent lido with epi, 6-0 Vicryl.
- God, I'm gonna ruin all the photographs.

491
00:27:24,543 --> 00:27:27,069
They won't look at you,
they'll be looking at the bride.

492
00:27:27,246 --> 00:27:29,238
- You owe me one.
- What? No, I don't.

493
00:27:29,414 --> 00:27:32,543
Yeah, you do. I put down
the NG on Mrs. Leerburger.

494
00:27:32,718 --> 00:27:34,016
I didn't ask you to do that.

495
00:27:34,186 --> 00:27:36,121
- Dr. Kovac did.
- What?

496
00:27:36,288 --> 00:27:40,749
He said you were a little
overextended today, unlike the rest of us.

497
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:44,359
Uh, Abby, will you excuse me?
I have to go yell at someone.

498
00:27:44,530 --> 00:27:46,089
Have fun.

499
00:27:46,398 --> 00:27:51,860
Okay, Miss Tobel, in the future, try not
to pluck your eyebrows in a moving car.

500
00:27:52,037 --> 00:27:55,303
Okay, numb and prep
the wound. I'll be right back.

501
00:27:56,675 --> 00:27:58,610
Get away from me! I
know what you want!

502
00:27:58,777 --> 00:28:00,939
- You wanna make me suffer!
- Security!

503
00:28:01,113 --> 00:28:05,312
- Lockhart, you're back. Welcome back.
- Thank you.

504
00:28:05,484 --> 00:28:09,387
I called John Manning at the International
Society for Traumatic Stress Studies...

505
00:28:09,555 --> 00:28:12,218
We're looking for our son.
We've been waiting for an hour.

506
00:28:12,391 --> 00:28:15,054
His name is Tevin. Tevin Burrough.
- Hold on. I'll check.

507
00:28:15,227 --> 00:28:17,890
We've been here an hour.
Where you going? Get back, bitch!

508
00:28:18,063 --> 00:28:20,589
Effective in the treatment
of traumatic disorders.

509
00:28:20,766 --> 00:28:23,463
You focus on the most vivid
image, emotion or sensation...

510
00:28:23,635 --> 00:28:27,402
in traumatic memory, simultaneously
focusing on an external impulse.

511
00:28:27,773 --> 00:28:31,801
I printed out a bunch of the studies
for you. You can take a look at them.

512
00:28:31,977 --> 00:28:35,414
- We can talk about them tomorrow.
- Okay, thank you.

513
00:28:35,581 --> 00:28:37,641
Good. Okay.

514
00:29:06,945 --> 00:29:08,607
Abby, eyebrow lac's ready.

515
00:29:08,780 --> 00:29:12,273
You were gonna show me
how to do a running subcuticular.

516
00:29:13,318 --> 00:29:14,650
Right.

517
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:17,051
- Are you okay?
- Yes. Yeah, I'm fine.

518
00:29:43,215 --> 00:29:45,013
This won't leave
a mark, will it?

519
00:29:45,183 --> 00:29:49,553
Dr. Lockhart is using a special
technique to minimize scarring.

520
00:29:56,495 --> 00:29:58,088
Abby?

521
00:30:01,199 --> 00:30:02,599
Um...

522
00:30:03,735 --> 00:30:06,227
I'm sorry. I can't
do this right now.

523
00:30:07,673 --> 00:30:10,336
What? ABBY: Sorry.

524
00:30:13,712 --> 00:30:16,011
- Joe, what happened?
- He threatened to sue me.

525
00:30:16,181 --> 00:30:17,581
He's parked in
front of a hydrant.

526
00:30:17,749 --> 00:30:19,160
What's with the motor home?

527
00:30:19,184 --> 00:30:20,846
I'm getting rid of it.

528
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,379
- Susan.
- Yeah?

529
00:30:23,555 --> 00:30:25,183
Uh, I think maybe I
came back too soon.

530
00:30:25,357 --> 00:30:26,620
- Are you okay?
- I don't know.

531
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:28,885
I'm not in the right
frame of mind to do this.

532
00:30:29,061 --> 00:30:31,724
- Take all the time you need.
- Ray's staying late to cover.

533
00:30:31,897 --> 00:30:34,696
No, it's okay. Don't worry
about it. I'll call you later.

534
00:30:40,839 --> 00:30:43,365
Sorry. Sorry.

535
00:30:49,147 --> 00:30:52,117
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

536
00:30:52,951 --> 00:30:54,647
God.

537
00:31:00,959 --> 00:31:03,087
You'll catch the next one.

538
00:31:04,796 --> 00:31:06,628
Thank you.

539
00:31:08,300 --> 00:31:10,269
Spivak, get out here now.

540
00:31:16,775 --> 00:31:19,609
- Hello, doctor.
- Oh, come on. We fixed you up.

541
00:31:21,646 --> 00:31:25,606
- Jerry.
- The guy has really great coffee.

542
00:31:28,954 --> 00:31:30,422
Sorry.

543
00:31:32,290 --> 00:31:33,588
Ahh.

544
00:31:33,759 --> 00:31:39,790
Dr. Lewis. Are you ready to
discuss this morning's fall?

545
00:31:43,034 --> 00:31:45,333
- Did you sign Mr. Fayen in to CT?
- Yeah.

546
00:31:45,504 --> 00:31:48,372
I had to go up to CT to push
morphine instead of doing it here.

547
00:31:48,540 --> 00:31:51,942
- Just trying to help.
- No. You're being passive-aggressive.

548
00:31:52,110 --> 00:31:53,544
- Why are you so mad?
- Because...

549
00:31:53,712 --> 00:31:56,011
I'm used to having control over my life.
- Sam.

550
00:31:56,181 --> 00:31:57,621
- What?
- Do you know where Neela is?

551
00:31:57,783 --> 00:31:59,308
No.

552
00:31:59,484 --> 00:32:01,680
You're the Attending on
Amy Packer, the foster kid?

553
00:32:01,853 --> 00:32:04,880
- Yeah.
- This is Mari Hinojosa from DCFS.

554
00:32:05,056 --> 00:32:06,319
I have bad news.

555
00:32:11,696 --> 00:32:14,131
- I think that's everything.
- Thank you.

556
00:32:14,299 --> 00:32:17,792
- "Desensitization reprocessing"?
- Yeah.

557
00:32:17,969 --> 00:32:20,200
It's some crazy stuff
Dubenko gave me.

558
00:32:21,072 --> 00:32:24,372
- Want me to give it a try?
- No. I think it's dead.

559
00:32:25,310 --> 00:32:26,869
Procrastinating.

560
00:32:31,550 --> 00:32:33,644
Didn't miss it at all.

561
00:32:34,886 --> 00:32:36,878
Work, over the holidays.

562
00:32:38,490 --> 00:32:42,393
I must've made an impression on you.
You didn't notice I was gone for a week.

563
00:32:42,828 --> 00:32:46,560
No, I remember. You're
the guy with the beard.

564
00:32:46,731 --> 00:32:48,199
Yeah.

565
00:32:49,034 --> 00:32:52,562
- Where did you go?
- Yellowstone.

566
00:32:52,737 --> 00:32:56,265
The most beautiful place
on earth. You ever been?

567
00:32:57,843 --> 00:33:01,041
I didn't realize it until I was smack
in the middle of the geysers...

568
00:33:01,213 --> 00:33:04,479
but the whole thing is actually
one gigantic active volcano.

569
00:33:05,083 --> 00:33:07,575
- Did you know that?
- No, I did not.

570
00:33:07,752 --> 00:33:12,281
It could blow at any second.
It's actually 30,000 years overdue.

571
00:33:13,225 --> 00:33:14,853
And what would happen if it did?

572
00:33:16,361 --> 00:33:19,126
It would wipe out most
of the western U.S.

573
00:33:19,297 --> 00:33:25,601
Cover the rest of the country in ash.
Wreak havoc on the global climate.

574
00:33:26,438 --> 00:33:27,680
Is that all?

575
00:33:27,704 --> 00:33:31,775
We'd be gone in an
instant, just like that.

576
00:33:31,943 --> 00:33:34,913
That's how fragile life is. You
know that. You work in the ER.

577
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:36,639
Yeah.

578
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:46,219
The human life span is so short
anyways. It's almost irrelevant.

579
00:33:46,558 --> 00:33:48,527
Are you high?

580
00:33:52,063 --> 00:33:53,895
There's your train.

581
00:33:56,935 --> 00:34:00,303
- See you later.
- Thank you.

582
00:34:03,308 --> 00:34:04,833
Bye.

583
00:34:13,084 --> 00:34:16,680
Between the paramedics and the doctors
here, we worked on him for 45 minutes...

584
00:34:16,855 --> 00:34:21,486
- but his injuries were too severe.
- His mother died when he was 5.

585
00:34:21,660 --> 00:34:25,597
Your son did well in surgery. They were
able to control the bleeding in his liver.

586
00:34:25,764 --> 00:34:28,728
Since then, it's just
been the two of us.

587
00:34:28,752 --> 00:34:31,670
He wasn't in pain,
and he didn't suffer.

588
00:34:31,836 --> 00:34:34,305
I knew something like
this was gonna happen.

589
00:34:35,340 --> 00:34:38,276
His heart and his brain were
spared. He'll probably do just fine.

590
00:34:38,577 --> 00:34:43,174
- He was talking about going to college.
- I'm very sorry.

591
00:34:55,493 --> 00:34:56,791
He's gonna be groggy...

592
00:34:56,962 --> 00:34:59,295
but he might be able to
hear what you're saying.

593
00:35:00,231 --> 00:35:02,325
Take as much time as
you need to say goodbye.

594
00:35:17,716 --> 00:35:19,412
This isn't my grandson.

595
00:35:19,718 --> 00:35:21,880
This isn't my son.

596
00:35:24,322 --> 00:35:25,346
Oh, God.

597
00:35:29,894 --> 00:35:31,226
Hello?

598
00:35:31,663 --> 00:35:33,029
Hi.

599
00:35:34,165 --> 00:35:39,229
No. No, they can't refuse to admit
her. She's got post-op adhesions.

600
00:35:39,404 --> 00:35:41,373
<i>The surgeon's gonna
rip our heads off...</i>

601
00:35:41,539 --> 00:35:42,734
Haleh.

602
00:35:43,008 --> 00:35:45,375
Haleh. Listen. Listen. Okay.

603
00:35:45,543 --> 00:35:49,344
Just push four of morphine,
and I'll be there in a minute, okay?

604
00:35:49,514 --> 00:35:51,380
- Fine. Bye.
- How the hell did this happen?

605
00:35:51,549 --> 00:35:53,541
- I'm not sure yet...
- Were they mislabeled?

606
00:35:53,718 --> 00:35:55,710
- I don't know.
- Did they look the same?

607
00:35:55,887 --> 00:35:57,879
- Was there a computer glitch?
- I don't know.

608
00:35:58,056 --> 00:36:00,184
All I know is that there
were two John Doe's...

609
00:36:00,358 --> 00:36:02,259
both 16, gunshot
wounds, gang-related.

610
00:36:02,427 --> 00:36:04,453
Both treated in Trauma
1 a few hours apart.

611
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:06,894
Susan, I just do not
understand how this happened.

612
00:36:07,065 --> 00:36:09,193
There was a massive
communication failure.

613
00:36:09,367 --> 00:36:12,235
Well, it's your job to make
sure that people communicate.

614
00:36:12,904 --> 00:36:16,238
I take full responsibility for it.
- We screwed up.

615
00:36:16,408 --> 00:36:18,104
We didn't know there
were two John Does.

616
00:36:18,276 --> 00:36:20,211
We didn't speak to each
other or check the board.

617
00:36:20,378 --> 00:36:21,573
Who was in which trauma?

618
00:36:21,746 --> 00:36:24,580
Neela, Sam and I worked on a
kid with a saphenous cutdown.

619
00:36:24,749 --> 00:36:26,581
Morris, Ray, Pratt
and I had the other.

620
00:36:26,751 --> 00:36:29,380
There was no overlap
between the traumas?

621
00:36:29,554 --> 00:36:31,113
I was in both.

622
00:36:31,756 --> 00:36:33,384
- Who's that?
- Med student.

623
00:36:33,558 --> 00:36:36,460
- I put a name alert on the board.
- Why didn't you say anything?

624
00:36:37,462 --> 00:36:40,557
No one listens to me. No one
even remembers I was in the room.

625
00:36:43,501 --> 00:36:46,767
- You look like you could use a vacation.
- No.

626
00:36:46,938 --> 00:36:51,569
I got this great time-share down in
Boca Grande that I let friends use.

627
00:36:51,743 --> 00:36:55,077
- Friends?
- You know, friends that refer friends.

628
00:36:55,447 --> 00:37:00,784
It's got a great house and this
beautiful boat and a pair of Jet Skis.

629
00:37:00,952 --> 00:37:02,250
Spivak? HERB: Ohh...

630
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:04,082
Security.

631
00:37:04,789 --> 00:37:07,315
Come on, give me
a break, will you?

632
00:37:11,329 --> 00:37:13,127
- You're back.
- Yep.

633
00:37:13,298 --> 00:37:16,598
- Thought your shift was over.
- No, not till 10.

634
00:37:16,768 --> 00:37:19,533
- So you were just taking a break?
- I guess so.

635
00:37:19,738 --> 00:37:21,969
- Up on the El tracks?
- Yeah.

636
00:37:22,307 --> 00:37:24,640
- I love it up there.
- Me too.

637
00:37:24,809 --> 00:37:27,142
Never know who
you might run into.

638
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:31,478
We just put them through
hell. What will you say?

639
00:37:31,649 --> 00:37:35,211
I'll tell the truth. Families of dead
patients don't remember much.

640
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:38,288
The only thing they remember
is if it seemed like you cared.

641
00:37:38,456 --> 00:37:41,551
If you were honest
and direct with them.

642
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:44,994
Did Dr. Lewis tell you to
keep me away from them?

643
00:37:46,131 --> 00:37:47,565
Yeah.

644
00:37:52,170 --> 00:37:56,471
- I wanna go in with you.
- Okay.

645
00:38:05,350 --> 00:38:07,683
It's unconstitutional.

646
00:38:08,386 --> 00:38:11,845
Thank you. Do not cross this
line, or I will have you arrested.

647
00:38:12,023 --> 00:38:14,015
- I don't see any line.
- You know what I mean.

648
00:38:14,192 --> 00:38:17,185
- You can't come back here.
- This is a public institution.

649
00:38:17,362 --> 00:38:21,197
- It doesn't matter.
- Well, you're violating my civil rights.

650
00:38:21,366 --> 00:38:23,335
I never got to see a doctor.

651
00:38:23,501 --> 00:38:24,594
So sue me.

652
00:38:24,803 --> 00:38:26,772
Your office is being
towed, by the way.

653
00:38:26,938 --> 00:38:29,203
Yo! Yo, yo, yo!

654
00:38:30,742 --> 00:38:35,407
Hold it, hold it, hold it. Come
on! Come on! Have some pity!

655
00:38:35,580 --> 00:38:39,881
- So much for Herb.
- Whatever. You know he'll be back.

656
00:38:44,856 --> 00:38:48,452
Amy? What's going on?

657
00:38:48,626 --> 00:38:50,026
- Who are you?
- I'm her doctor.

658
00:38:50,195 --> 00:38:52,562
- I'm bringing her to the Haley Home.
- She lied to me.

659
00:38:52,730 --> 00:38:55,461
- Go talk to your social worker.
- I don't understand. Stop.

660
00:38:55,633 --> 00:38:58,398
I have two more kids to pick
up. Don't make my job any harder.

661
00:38:58,570 --> 00:39:01,404
- Amy, wait.
- She told me I could go home.

662
00:39:04,409 --> 00:39:07,311
- Thirty days?
- You can have visitors after two weeks.

663
00:39:07,478 --> 00:39:10,778
- I need to talk to you.
- Cold turkey, just like that?

664
00:39:10,949 --> 00:39:13,748
Well, they give you medication
to help ease the withdrawal.

665
00:39:13,918 --> 00:39:15,910
Think about it, okay?

666
00:39:17,422 --> 00:39:19,914
How could you pull Amy out
of her home behind my back?

667
00:39:20,091 --> 00:39:22,424
It wasn't behind your back.
We got new information.

668
00:39:22,594 --> 00:39:24,893
- We had a plan.
- Her caseworker was out of town...

669
00:39:25,063 --> 00:39:27,726
- Why didn't you tell me?
- If you would stop interrupting...

670
00:39:27,899 --> 00:39:31,927
- You're supposed to consult the doctor...
- Kovac signed off.

671
00:39:32,270 --> 00:39:36,765
- Hey.
- I'm hating doctors right now.

672
00:39:36,941 --> 00:39:39,604
Neela's mad, Ray practically
accused me of elder abuse.

673
00:39:39,777 --> 00:39:42,269
Morris laughed when this
kid kicked me in the shin.

674
00:39:42,447 --> 00:39:45,645
- I was gonna ask if you were ready.
- That's all you have to say?

675
00:39:45,817 --> 00:39:48,480
You know, we come from
different perspectives sometimes...

676
00:39:48,653 --> 00:39:52,454
and sometimes we disagree. But
whatever happened, you were right.

677
00:39:52,624 --> 00:39:54,957
- Why didn't you tell me about Amy?
- I was going to.

678
00:39:55,126 --> 00:39:56,321
- When?
- When I had time.

679
00:39:56,494 --> 00:39:59,123
Thought it might be better if
you found out after your shift.

680
00:39:59,297 --> 00:40:01,323
I'm an adult. I don't
need you to protect me.

681
00:40:01,499 --> 00:40:05,300
I wasn't trying to. You made a good
decision based on information you had.

682
00:40:05,470 --> 00:40:07,939
- But there was a pattern of incidents.
- Like what?

683
00:40:09,941 --> 00:40:12,789
Like April 16th, scald
injury to shoulder.

684
00:40:12,813 --> 00:40:14,641
Sounds pretty minor to me.

685
00:40:14,812 --> 00:40:18,806
- July 14th, bite inflicted by brother.
- Who we know has behavioral issues.

